<br>
Droga had exactly one person in it (The majority of the server are cowards, it appears). This was a level 63 mage who had used the levitation trick to get up on the exit ledge. So yes, both dungeons are still one way dungeons. Cast levitation on yourself repeatedly, and you can reach that ledge. Supposedly anyway, untested by me. He said that the goblins were tough. I didn't fight any in Droga.<br>
<br>
I watched him kill a goblin. The goblin, a shaman, was hitting for around 200. He killed it fairly easily, though it was doing a decent number on his pet (he was using whatever level 63 mages use as an air pet). He said the goblins were dropping a minimum of 12 plat apiece, and he saw one drop 20. The guy wasn't interested in partnering, nor was he particularly talkative.<br>
<br>
So, I headed to Nurga, not being willing to risk my life without knowing whether invisibility worked. I saw nothing in Nurga that could see through my invis. Mobs immediatly to the left, at the bottom of the waterfall, were light blue at 58. Moving even slightly further in, they became dark blue. There were 2 groups of low 50's (50 to 53 or so, in levels) hunting the dungeon. They rated xp as &quot;good&quot;. <br>
<br>
I did not go deep into the dungeon (no time). I did kill 20 or so goblins before I left. At 58, to solo as a beastlord, these guys are cake. You have Wizards, SK's, shamans, warriors and rogue mobs. None presented a challenge. The SK's have a 500 point harm touch. I could kill them with very little downtime. The XP was noticably better than Katta guards, and the gobbies were easier to kill. XP was about the same as in a full group in Plane of Nightmare, at the werewolves. I don't do that wimpy % stuff on the xp bar, so I can't tell you what % per kill they were. They dropped from 6 gold, to 7 plat. Average was 6 plat or so per kill. <br>
<br>
It was *very* easy to single pull them. Their assist range is much, much smaller than it was in the old Nurga, even when they were hunted at the proper level (dark blue to a level 35 for instance). I saw the standard Chardok faction drops - the salts, insignia, etc. I got no items.<br>
<br>
All told, I'll hazard that Sony took two underused 30-40 zones, and has turned them into two underused 50-65 zones. I blame this entirely on wimpy players. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
